### A dulcimer voice (plucked, metallic)

A hammered dulcimer has a bright attack and a ringing, metallic sustain. We can approximate that with strong mid and high harmonics.

*[needs: GAP-4]*

```scheme
(define dulcimer-voice
  (create-periodic-wave
    (list 1.0      ;; 1st
          0.4      ;; 2nd
          0.7      ;; 3rd, strong
          0.3      ;; 4th
          0.6      ;; 5th, strong
          0.25     ;; 6th
          0.5      ;; 7th, strong
          0.2      ;; 8th
          0.4      ;; 9th, moderate
          0.15     ;; 10th
          0.3      ;; 11th, moderate
          0.1)))   ;; 12th

(note/strike 67 'quarter 0.75 dulcimer-voice)  ;; G4, bright and ringing
```

The strong odd and mid harmonics give it that **bright, shimmering** plucked-metal character.

