          0.6      ;; 3rd, strong
          0.4      ;; 4th, moderate
          0.5      ;; 5th, strong
          0.35     ;; 6th, moderate
          0.4      ;; 7th, moderate
          0.25     ;; 8th, fading
          0.3      ;; 9th, fading
          0.2)))   ;; 10th, faint

(note/strike 64 'eighth 0.8 harpsichord-voice)  ;; E4, bright pluck
```

The many mid-range harmonics give it that **bright, plucked** character. (In a full implementation, we'd pair this with a sharp ADSR envelope *[needs: GAP-8]* for the percussive attack.)

