### Playing a melody with a custom voice

Now let's take one of our voices and play a short melody with it. We'll use the **cello-section** voice and play a four-note descending phrase.

*[needs: GAP-4]*

```scheme
(define cello-section
  (create-periodic-wave
    (list 1.0 0.6 0.4 0.25 0.15 0.08 0.04 0.02)))

(define (descending-phrase)
  (note/strike 60 'quarter 0.75 cello-section)  ;; C4
  (note/strike 58 'quarter 0.7 cello-section)   ;; Bb3
  (note/strike 55 'quarter 0.7 cello-section)   ;; G3
  (note/strike 53 'half 0.8 cello-section))     ;; F3

(descending-phrase)
```

<!-- BUILD: wire this so the four notes play in sequence, each using the cello-section voice. -->

You hear a warm, rich descending line — one synthesized voice, but it feels like a section of cellos playing together.

