### A voice with exponential harmonic decay

Instead of `1/n`, use `e^(-n)` for a **very fast** rolloff.

```scheme
(define exp-decay-profile
  (list 0.0
        (exp 0)
        (exp -1)
        (exp -2)
        (exp -3)
        (exp -4)
        (exp -5)
        (exp -6)))

;; *[needs: GAP-6]*
;; (define-voice 'exp-decay (exp-decay-profile '(0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0)))

(define (exp-decay-melody)
  (note 60 'quarter 75)
  (note 64 'quarter 75)
  (note 67 'quarter 75)
  (note 72 'quarter 75))

(exp-decay-melody)
```

<!-- BUILD: extremely soft, almost sine-like -->

[VISUAL: Spectrum with a very sharp exponential decay — the tail drops off almost instantly. Label: \"Exponential decay — very fast rolloff.\"]

---


### A voice with random harmonic phases

Same magnitudes, but **randomize the phase** of each harmonic (via the imaginary components).

```scheme
(define random-phase-real
  '(0.0 1.0 0.5 0.4 0.3 0.2 0.15 0.1))

(define random-phase-imag
  '(0.0 0.0 0.3 -0.2 0.4 -0.1 0.2 -0.3))

;; *[needs: GAP-6]*
;; (define-voice 'random-phase (random-phase-real random-phase-imag))

(define (random-phase-tone)
  (note 60 'whole 80))

(random-phase-tone)
```

<!-- BUILD: same spectrum as a normal voice, but the waveform is scrambled — subtle timbre shift -->

[VISUAL: Two waveforms — one with aligned phases, one with randomized phases. Same spectrum, different shapes. Label: \"Random phase — same spectrum, scrambled waveform.\"]

