### A voice built from the golden ratio

Use **φ** (phi, the golden ratio ≈ 1.618) to weight harmonics.

```scheme
(define phi 1.618033988749895)

(define golden-profile
  (list 0.0 1.0 (/ 1.0 phi) (/ 1.0 (* phi phi))
        (/ 1.0 (* phi phi phi)) (/ 1.0 (* phi phi phi phi))))

;; *[needs: GAP-6]*
;; (define-voice 'golden (golden-profile '(0 0 0 0 0 0)))

(define (golden-chord)
  (note 48 'whole 80)
  (note 55 'whole 80)
  (note 60 'whole 80))

(golden-chord)
```

<!-- BUILD: a \"naturally\" decaying spectrum based on the golden ratio -->

[VISUAL: Spectrum with harmonics decaying by powers of φ. Label: \"Golden ratio decay.\"]

---


### A voice with a square-root decay

Harmonic amplitudes decay as `1/√n`.

```scheme
(define sqrt-decay-profile
  (list 0.0 1.0 (/ 1.0 (sqrt 2)) (/ 1.0 (sqrt 3))
        (/ 1.0 (sqrt 4)) (/ 1.0 (sqrt 5)) (/ 1.0 (sqrt 6))))

;; *[needs: GAP-6]*
;; (define-voice 'sqrt-decay (sqrt-decay-profile '(0 0 0 0 0 0 0)))

(define (sqrt-decay-melody)
  (note 60 'quarter 75)
  (note 64 'quarter 75)
  (note 67 'quarter 75)
  (note 72 'quarter 75))

(sqrt-decay-melody)
```

<!-- BUILD: slower decay than 1/n, richer than 1/n² -->

[VISUAL: Spectrum with a smooth √n decay curve. Label: \"Square-root decay — slower than 1/n.\"]

